After deploying code dozens of times this season, we can no longer deploy code to our roboRIO 1. We get this error:

Execution failed for task ':deployfrcJavaroborio'.
    > A failure occurred while executing edu.wpi.first.deployutils.deploy.artifact.ArtifactDeployWorker
        > SFTP error (SSH_FX_FAILURE): Failure

Per a suggestion in a post to NIâ€™s forums, we have tried reformatting the roboRIO. Fails.

We have tried reapplying the firmware to the roboRIO. Also fails.

We are stone dead in the water.

Anybody have any idea what is going on here?

Its possible you either have too many logs stored, or your deploy folder is too large.
